"n.正式演说，演讲 【英】 n. 正式演说，演讲(a formal public speech) 【记】 orate(演说)+ion→演 说 无 【记】orate 演说 + tion；O 象个嘴 + rate 评价，认为，用嘴来评价→演说 oration (n.)  late 14c., ""prayer,"" from Late Latin orationem (nominative oratio) ""a speaking, speech, discourse; language, faculty of speech, mode of expressing; prayer,"" noun of action from past participle stem of Latin orare ""to pray, plead, speak before an assembly"" (see orator). Meaning ""formal speech, discourse"" first recorded c.1500."
